{"id": "EUVD-2025-22846", "enisaUuid": "5546cfbc-0220-3d1c-9f01-22aae2d90cb2", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/sched: fix use-after-free in taprio_dev_notifier\n\nSince taprio\u2019s taprio_dev_notifier() isn\u2019t protected by an\nRCU read-side critical section, a race with advance_sched()\ncan lead to a use-after-free.\n\nAdding rcu_read_lock() inside taprio_dev_notifier() prevents this.", "datePublished": "2025-06-30T09:30:24", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T15:31:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8c5713ce1ced75f9e9ed5c642ea3d2ba06ead69c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8a008c89e5e5c5332e4c0a33d707db9ddd529f8a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b1547d28ba468bc3b88764efd13e4319bab63be8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b160766e26d4e2e2d6fe2294e0b02f92baefcec5", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38087"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38087"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0209187e-f07c-39ca-9d69-ac65d4610d3b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fed87cc6718ad5f80aa739fee3c5979a8b09d3a6 <b160766e26d4e2e2d6fe2294e0b02f92baefcec5"}, {"id": "3123c64e-3000-3bc6-a28e-e82621246dc3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.3"}, {"id": "4933e96e-bf5e-3830-babf-f64e9776e07e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fed87cc6718ad5f80aa739fee3c5979a8b09d3a6 <8c5713ce1ced75f9e9ed5c642ea3d2ba06ead69c"}, {"id": "5edf495d-351f-3251-995f-61ab8a859811", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.4"}, {"id": "6ada124e-b994-3237-a50d-5a463d38c76b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "8162a2a3-822b-38e6-9f4d-55d5a383b316", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.95"}, {"id": "ba75a3bf-d746-339b-886d-ebec696e79b2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "fed87cc6718ad5f80aa739fee3c5979a8b09d3a6 <b1547d28ba468bc3b88764efd13e4319bab63be8"}, {"i